  "text": "C Vortex current distribution J V+I (x, y) can be derived as follows [CITATION_1] . A current associated with a vortex near a surface satisfies the boundary condition of zero current normal to the surface. Such a current distribution can be reproduced by removing the surface and introducing an appropriate image antivortex. Then the total vortex current is given by a summation of currents due to a vortex and an image antivortex on an infinite SC without a surface. Since the vortex and the image antivortex on the w-plane are located at w = +iǫ ≃ i(αξ/K 1 ) 1 α and −iǫ, respectively, the total vortex current distribution on the w-plane, J V+I , is given by",
